modules.description: This module executes HTTP requests over a provided connection flow, handling both HTTP/1.1 and HTTP/2 protocols. It processes responses incrementally using a user-supplied function and supports TLS and TCP flows for secure and unencrypted communication. Use it to fetch resources from web servers, handle redirects, or stream response data directly.

This module implements an HTTP server that handles incoming requests using the Miou scheduler. It supports HTTP/1.1 and HTTP/2 protocols over TCP or TLS, with configurable backends and error handling. The server processes requests through user-defined handlers, allowing direct manipulation of connections, request metadata, and response writing.

This module implements an HTTP client and server with support for HTTP/1.1 and HTTP/2 protocols over TCP or TLS. It provides functions to send requests with customizable methods, headers, and body content, handling redirects and using the happy-eyeballs algorithm for connection establishment. Concrete use cases include fetching remote resources, streaming response data, and building custom HTTP services with direct control over request handling and connection management.
